
[1]adjacency

   ADJA'CENCY, n. [L. adjaceo, to lie contiguous, from ad and jaceo, to
   lie.]

   The state of lying close or contiguous; a bordering upon, or lying next
   to; as the adjacency of lands or buildings. In the sense of that which
   is adjacent, as used by Brown, it is not legitimate.
